commit.message: libhfuzz: fix HF_strlcpy so it matches the strlcpy spec (ret value)
libhfuzz: fix strlcat wrapper
mangle: revert e77f7604a0abc6b85c399b6efd8b55be26ccd9d6 as the old behavior seems to give better results
cmdline: initialize a few vars
.cland: add -D_HF_ARCH_LINUX
linux/bfd: cast a function of an incompatible type via void*
.cland: treat all files as C, as clangd sometimes recognizes .h as objective-c
linux/bfd: allow un-strict function conversion with clang
linux/bfd: define 'enum fake_disassembler_style' in case the real 'enum disassembler_style' is not defined in older dis-asm.h
cmdline: log '-h/--help' to stdout instead of stderr
libhfcommon: include other libhfcommon *.h's without the directory prefix
.clangd: for nvim clangd module
clang-format: IndentCaseLabels: false
